Source: https://context7.com/mvdan/gofumpt/llms.txt

The format.Options struct allows fine-grained control over gofumpt's formatting behavior. Key options include LangVersion to target specific Go language versions, affecting rules like octal literal formatting. ModulePath is used to group imports, treating paths matching the prefix as third-party. Extra formatting rules, such as grouping adjacent parameters with the same type or adding explicit return values to naked returns, can also be enabled.

